nodes.text: Hello Person1. Yep, just got a call for MM/DD/YYYY w Dr. B on MM/DD/YYYY. Re Oxy 15mg rapid release: per Dr. Person2's desire and Dr. B agree to get Person3 off Oxy ext release ASAP, and work down to lowest usage Oxy rapid w/o dealing w break through pain, which can be pretty nasty. I've set up Person3's other am, MM/DD/YYYY, pm meds w 7.5mg Oxy 3x diem, with 7.5 Oxy boosters once, twice a day as needed. Trying to keep Oxy steady at MM/DD/YYYY, but MM/DD/YYYY had to go MM/DD/YYYY. 30 count has gotten him through MM/DD/YYYY, considering ste p down and a few tough pain MM/DD/YYYY thereafter. Re Eliquis: MM/DD/YYYY two 5mg tabs morning and night; MM/DD/YYYY one 5mg am and one 5mg pm. Sig swelling (but improving slightly) swelling of right leg persists. Person3 is tolerating all meds well and following directions. Appetite, a bit of a struggle, as expected; digestion normal (that may become diarrhea as radiation has started MM/DD/YYYY). Dr. B recommends Metamucil 1 tsp 2x diem. Other symptoms: quite tired, napping, MM/DD/YYYY recently interrupted by anxiety attacks. Thanks a ton, Person1, best – Person4
